apiVersion: sandbox.enterprise.ai/v1alpha1
kind: AgentWorkflow
metadata:
  name: mobile-daw
  namespace: default
spec:
  description: >
    Build BeatForge — a mobile step sequencer, drum machine, and synthesizer
    using React Native + Expo. Four steps: tooling (lint, test, WAV generation),
    foundation (architecture + engines + stores + wiring), implement (all UI
    components + screens), polish (fix everything + integration trace + tests).
    Steps share a workspace and pass structured handoff state between them.
  input: >
    Build "BeatForge" — a mobile DAW app with step sequencer, drum pads,
    synthesizer, and mixer. React Native 0.76+, Expo SDK 52, TypeScript strict,
    expo-av for audio, Zustand 5, expo-router, react-native-reanimated.
    Target iOS 16+ / Android 12+. Dark theme (#0a0a0a bg, #ff6b35 accent).
    App Store ready. Zustand 5 uses NAMED import: import { create } from 'zustand'.
    Use STATIC require() maps for all audio assets — no dynamic require().
    NEVER create shim .d.ts files. See project context for full specification.
  contextRef: mobile-daw-context
  messageBus: in-memory

  steps:
    # ── Step 0: Tooling Setup ─────────────────────────────────────────────
    # Why this step exists: The original workflow had no ESLint, no Prettier,
    # no test runner, and no WAV generation. All four cause downstream failures:
    # bad types slip through, hooks violations crash the app, empty WAV files
    # mean audio never plays. This step creates the infrastructure first so
    # subsequent steps are verified continuously.
    - name: tooling
      type: agent
      agentRef: daw-agent
      prompt: |
        Read the project context (mobile-daw-context ConfigMap) and ALL
        skill files before writing a single line of code.

        Your job: establish the complete project tooling foundation in /workspace/.
        After this step, TypeScript checking, linting, formatting, testing, and
        audio asset generation all work. Subsequent steps depend on this.

        ## Task 1 — package.json with complete devDependencies
        Create /workspace/package.json. Include ALL of the following:

        Runtime dependencies:
          expo: ~52.0.0
          expo-router: ~4.0.0
          react-native: 0.76.3
          expo-av: ~14.0.0
          react-native-reanimated: ~3.16.0
          react-native-gesture-handler: ~2.20.0
          react-native-safe-area-context: ~4.12.0
          react-native-screens: ~4.1.0
          expo-haptics: ~14.0.0
          expo-font: ~13.0.0
          expo-splash-screen: ~0.29.0
          expo-status-bar: ~2.0.0
          expo-constants: ~17.0.0
          "@react-native-async-storage/async-storage": ~2.1.0
          zustand: ^5.0.0
          react-native-svg: ~15.8.0
          "@expo/vector-icons": ~14.0.0

        devDependencies (ALL required):
          typescript: ~5.6.0
          "@types/react": ~18.3.0
          "@types/react-native": ~0.73.0
          eslint: ~8.57.0
          "@typescript-eslint/eslint-plugin": ~7.18.0
          "@typescript-eslint/parser": ~7.18.0
          eslint-plugin-react-hooks: ~4.6.0
          prettier: ~3.3.0
          jest: ~29.7.0
          jest-expo: ~52.0.0
          "@testing-library/react-native": ~12.8.0
          "@types/jest": ~29.5.0

        scripts:
          start: expo start
          android: expo run:android
          ios: expo run:ios
          web: expo start --web
          typecheck: tsc --noEmit
          lint: eslint --ext .ts,.tsx src/
          lint:fix: eslint --ext .ts,.tsx src/ --fix
          format: prettier --write "src/**/*.{ts,tsx}"
          test: jest --watchAll=false
          generate-samples: node scripts/generate-samples.js

        jest config in package.json:
          "jest": {
            "preset": "jest-expo",
            "transformIgnorePatterns": [
              "node_modules/(?!((jest-)?react-native|@react-native(-community)?)|expo(nent)?|@expo(nent)?/.*|@expo-google-fonts/.*|react-navigation|@react-navigation/.*|@unimodules/.*|unimodules|sentry-expo|native-base|react-native-svg)"
            ]
          }

        ## Task 2 — tsconfig.json
        Create /workspace/tsconfig.json:
          {
            "extends": "expo/tsconfig.base",
            "compilerOptions": {
              "strict": true,
              "noImplicitAny": true,
              "strictNullChecks": true,
              "noUnusedLocals": true,
              "noUnusedParameters": true,
              "exactOptionalPropertyTypes": false,
              "baseUrl": ".",
              "paths": {
                "@/*": ["src/*"]
              }
            },
            "include": ["src/**/*", "scripts/**/*"],
            "exclude": ["node_modules"]
          }

        ## Task 3 — .eslintrc.json
        Create /workspace/.eslintrc.json:
          {
            "root": true,
            "parser": "@typescript-eslint/parser",
            "parserOptions": { "project": "./tsconfig.json" },
            "plugins": ["@typescript-eslint", "react-hooks"],
            "extends": [
              "eslint:recommended",
              "plugin:@typescript-eslint/recommended",
              "plugin:react-hooks/recommended"
            ],
            "rules": {
              "@typescript-eslint/no-explicit-any": "error",
              "@typescript-eslint/no-var-requires": "off",
              "react-hooks/rules-of-hooks": "error",
              "react-hooks/exhaustive-deps": "warn",
              "no-console": ["warn", { "allow": ["error", "warn"] }]
            },
            "ignorePatterns": ["node_modules/", "scripts/"]
          }

        ## Task 4 — .prettierrc
        Create /workspace/.prettierrc:
          { "semi": true, "singleQuote": true, "trailingComma": "es5",
            "printWidth": 100, "tabWidth": 2, "bracketSpacing": true }

        ## Task 5 — app.json (Expo config)
        Create /workspace/app.json:
          {
            "expo": {
              "name": "BeatForge",
              "slug": "beatforge",
              "version": "0.1.0",
              "orientation": "portrait",
              "icon": "./assets/icon.png",
              "userInterfaceStyle": "dark",
              "splash": {
                "image": "./assets/splash.png",
                "resizeMode": "contain",
                "backgroundColor": "#0a0a0a"
              },
              "ios": {
                "supportsTablet": false,
                "bundleIdentifier": "com.beatforge.app",
                "buildNumber": "1",
                "infoPlist": {
                  "UIBackgroundModes": ["audio"],
                  "NSMicrophoneUsageDescription": "BeatForge does not use the microphone."
                }
              },
              "android": {
                "package": "com.beatforge.app",
                "versionCode": 1,
                "adaptiveIcon": {
                  "foregroundImage": "./assets/adaptive-icon.png",
                  "backgroundColor": "#0a0a0a"
                },
                "permissions": []
              },
              "plugins": [
                "expo-router",
                "expo-av",
                ["expo-splash-screen", { "backgroundColor": "#0a0a0a" }]
              ],
              "experiments": { "typedRoutes": true }
            }
          }

        ## Task 6 — eas.json
        Create /workspace/eas.json with development, preview, production profiles.

        ## Task 7 — WAV generation script
        Create /workspace/scripts/generate-samples.js using EXACTLY the script
        from the audio-engine skill. Then RUN it immediately:
          node scripts/generate-samples.js
        Verify output: ls -la /workspace/assets/samples/ — every file must be > 1000 bytes.

        ## Task 8 — Jest mock setup
        Create /workspace/src/test-utils/setup.ts:
          // Global mock for expo-av — allows engine tests to run without a device
          jest.mock('expo-av', () => ({
            Audio: {
              Sound: jest.fn().mockImplementation(() => ({
                loadAsync: jest.fn().mockResolvedValue({}),
                replayAsync: jest.fn().mockResolvedValue({}),
                setStatusAsync: jest.fn().mockResolvedValue({}),
                stopAsync: jest.fn().mockResolvedValue({}),
                unloadAsync: jest.fn().mockResolvedValue({}),
              })),
              setAudioModeAsync: jest.fn().mockResolvedValue({}),
            },
            InterruptionModeIOS: { DoNotMix: 0, MixWithOthers: 2 },
            InterruptionModeAndroid: { DuckOthers: 1, DoNotMix: 0 },
          }));
          jest.mock('@react-native-async-storage/async-storage', () =>
            require('@react-native-async-storage/async-storage/jest/async-storage-mock')
          );

        ## Verification
        Run npm install first (to get dependencies), then:
          node scripts/generate-samples.js
          npx tsc --noEmit
          ls -la assets/samples/
        Confirm all WAV files are > 1000 bytes. If npm install fails due to
        network, note the error but continue creating all config files.

        ## Handoff state (write this JSON to /workspace/.workflow-state.json):
          {
            "step": "tooling",
            "completed": true,
            "wavFilesGenerated": true,
            "tscClean": true,
            "eslintConfigured": true,
            "sampleFiles": ["kick.wav","snare.wav","hihat.wav","clap.wav",
                           "tom.wav","perc.wav","bass_synth_C3.wav","lead_synth_C4.wav"]
          }
      execution:
        timeoutSeconds: 300
        maxAttempts: 1
        retryable: false
        continueOnError: false
        maxTurns: 4
        sessionGroup: dev-session

    # ── Step 1: Foundation ────────────────────────────────────────────────
    # Why changes from original:
    # - Added sampleRequires.ts as a required file (fixes Metro dynamic require)
    # - Explicit Zustand v5 import syntax in every store template
    # - Drift-correcting clock from audio-engine skill (replaces naive setInterval)
    # - loadProject() syncs engine not just store (fixes dual-state divergence)
    # - makeEmptySteps typed as Record<string,Step[]> not Record<string,any>
    # - maxTurns raised from 5 to 8 to allow proper verification
    - name: foundation
      type: agent
      agentRef: daw-agent
      dependsOn:
        - tooling
      prompt: |
        Read /workspace/.workflow-state.json to confirm tooling is complete.
        Read the project context (mobile-daw-context ConfigMap) and ALL skill
        files — especially known-pitfalls, audio-engine, and integration-wiring.

        Build the complete logic layer: types, constants, engine modules, stores,
        and the wiring hook. After this step, `npx tsc --noEmit` passes with
        zero errors and all 10 pitfall checks pass.

        ## PHASE A — Foundation Files

        ### A1: src/constants/sampleRequires.ts  ← MUST BE FIRST
        CRITICAL: This file must exist before AudioEngine.ts.
        Use EXACTLY the SAMPLE_REQUIRES pattern from the audio-engine skill.
        Every require() call must be a literal static string.
        No variables, no concatenation, no template literals in require().

        ### A2: src/types/index.ts
        Use the complete type definitions from the project context.
        Key types: Step, Pattern, Track, SynthParams, MixerChannel,
        TransportState, Project, TrackType, Waveform.
        NO `any` anywhere. NO shim files.

        ### A3: src/constants/theme.ts
        Export COLORS, SPACING, FONT_SIZES as named exports.
        Colors: background '#0a0a0a', surface '#1a1a1a', accent '#ff6b35',
                secondary '#00d4aa', text '#e0e0e0', muted '#666666'.

        ### A4: src/constants/defaults.ts
        Export DEFAULT_TRACKS (8 tracks: kick, snare, hihat, clap, tom, perc,
        bass, lead), DEFAULT_PATTERN, DEFAULT_SYNTH_PARAMS.
        makeEmptySteps MUST return Record<string, Step[]>, not Record<string, any>.
        Function signature: makeEmptySteps(tracks: Track[]): Record<string, Step[]>

        ### A5: src/utils/timing.ts
        stepDurationMs(bpm: number): number — 60000 / bpm / 4
        swingOffset(stepIndex: number, swing: number, stepMs: number): number
        bpmToMs(bpm: number): number

        ### A6: src/utils/colors.ts
        withOpacity(hex: string, alpha: number): string
        lighten(hex: string, percent: number): string

        ## PHASE B — Engine Layer
        Follow the audio-engine skill EXACTLY. Do not improvise patterns.

        ### B1: src/engine/AudioEngine.ts
        - Singleton with getInstance()
        - init() uses InterruptionModeIOS.DoNotMix (NOT deprecated constant)
        - preloadSamples() iterates SAMPLE_REQUIRES from sampleRequires.ts
          (NO dynamic require, NO string concatenation)
        - Pool size: 4 sounds per sample key
        - resume(), suspend(), setMasterVolume(), getMasterVolume(), getPool()

        ### B2: src/engine/SequencerClock.ts
        MUST use the drift-correcting pattern from the audio-engine skill.
        Key fields: nextStepTime, lookahead tick loop.
        NOT a simple setInterval(() => fire(), stepMs) — that drifts.
        start(bpm, swing), stop(), onStep(cb), tick() private method.

        ### B3: src/engine/SamplerEngine.ts
        Pool-based playback from the audio-engine skill.
        play(sampleKey, velocity, volume, pan) — uses pool rotation.
        stop(sampleKey) — stops all pool sounds for that key.

        ### B4: src/engine/SynthEngine.ts
        Simple note player using pre-loaded samples.
        NOTE_MAP: Record<string, ReturnType<typeof require>> using static
        require() calls — same Metro constraint as AudioEngine.
        play(note, velocity), stopAll(), preloadNotes(): Promise<void>.
        Document clearly in a comment that real-time synthesis is not
        possible with expo-av; this uses pre-rendered samples.

        ### B5: src/engine/MixerEngine.ts
        channels: Map<string, MixerChannel> (import MixerChannel from types)
        initChannels(tracks), setVolume, setPan, setMute, setSolo.
        getEffectiveVolume(trackId): number — considers mute AND solo correctly:
          - If any channel has solo=true: only soloed and unmuted channels
            return their volume; all others return 0.
          - If no channel is soloed: muted channels return 0, others their volume.
        MUST NOT have duplicate state — the Map is the single source of truth.

        ## PHASE C — Stores
        CRITICAL: Every store uses `import { create } from 'zustand'` (named import).
        NEVER `import create from 'zustand'`.

        ### C1: src/stores/transportStore.ts
        Implement using the v5 pattern from the strict-types skill.
        play() MUST call: AudioEngine.getInstance().resume() THEN
          SequencerClock.getInstance().start(bpm, swing) THEN set({ isPlaying: true })
        stop() MUST call: SequencerClock.getInstance().stop() THEN
          set({ isPlaying: false, currentStep: 0 })
        setBpm() MUST restart clock if isPlaying.
        setSwing() MUST restart clock if isPlaying.
        tapTempo(): calculate from lastTaps[], update bpm, restart if playing.

        ### C2: src/stores/sequencerStore.ts
        patterns, tracks, currentPatternId.
        toggleStep(trackId, stepIndex): immutable update via set().
        setVelocity(trackId, stepIndex, velocity): immutable update.
        setCurrentPatternId(id: string): set({ currentPatternId: id }).
          ← this action MUST exist so components can call it through set()
        getCurrentPattern(): Pattern — returns current or first pattern.
        copyPattern, clearPattern, addTrack, removeTrack.

        ### C3: src/stores/mixerStore.ts
        Every action calls the corresponding MixerEngine method AND then set().
        setVolume → MixerEngine.setVolume() + set()
        setPan → MixerEngine.setPan() + set()
        setMute → MixerEngine.setMute() + set()
        setSolo → MixerEngine.setSolo() + set()
        setMasterVolume → AudioEngine.setMasterVolume() + set()

        ### C4: src/stores/synthStore.ts
        params: Record<string, SynthParams> (NOT Record<string, any>).
        setParams(id: string, params: SynthParams): immutable update.
        setWaveform(id: string, waveform: Waveform): partial update.

        ### C5: src/stores/projectStore.ts
        saveProject(): serialize transport + sequencer + mixer + synth to AsyncStorage.
        loadProject(): deserialize AND sync BOTH stores AND engines.
          After loading mixer state: iterate channels and call MixerEngine methods.
          See project context "FAILURE MODE 5" for the exact required pattern.
        Error handling: wrap JSON.parse in try/catch, log errors.

        ## PHASE D — Wiring Hook

        ### D1: src/hooks/useAudioSetup.ts
        Follow the integration-wiring skill EXACTLY.
        The onStep callback is the most critical piece — use the exact
        implementation from the skill.
        Returns: { isReady: boolean, error: string | null }
        Cleanup on unmount: stop the clock.
        Called ONLY in root _layout.tsx, never in tab screens.

        ## PHASE E — Verification (MUST complete all gates)

        Run gates in this order. Fix any failures before declaring done.

        ```bash
        # Gate 7: Zustand imports
        grep -rn "^import create from 'zustand'" /workspace/src/
        # Must be EMPTY — any match = fail

        # Gate 8: No dynamic require
        grep -rn "require(.*+\|require(\`" /workspace/src/
        # Must be EMPTY

        # Gate 9: Engine wiring
        grep -c "AudioEngine\|SequencerClock" /workspace/src/stores/transportStore.ts
        # Must be >= 4

        # Gate 1: TypeScript
        cd /workspace && npx tsc --noEmit
        # Must be zero errors

        # Gate 5: No any
        grep -rn ": any\b\|as any\|<any>" /workspace/src/
        # Must be EMPTY

        # Gate 10: Real WAV files
        ls -la /workspace/assets/samples/*.wav | awk '{print $5, $9}'
        # Every file must be > 1000 bytes
        ```

        ## Handoff state (update /workspace/.workflow-state.json):
          {
            "step": "foundation",
            "completed": true,
            "tscClean": true,
            "storeCount": <number>,
            "engineCount": <number>,
            "wiringGatesPassed": true,
            "filesCreated": [<list all created src files>]
          }
      execution:
        timeoutSeconds: 720
        maxAttempts: 1
        retryable: false
        continueOnError: false
        maxTurns: 8
        sessionGroup: dev-session

    # ── Step 2: Implement UI ──────────────────────────────────────────────
    # Why changes from original:
    # - Added StepCell as separate memo'd component (avoids hooks-in-map)
    # - Added explicit pattern for Knob/Fader with startValue (fixes stale props)
    # - Settings screen now has explicit required controls list
    # - Added PadButton memo'd component pattern
    # - maxTurns raised from 8 to 10
    # - Every screen must call useAudioSetup ONLY through _layout.tsx (not themselves)
    - name: implement
      type: agent
      agentRef: daw-agent
      dependsOn:
        - foundation
      prompt: |
        Read /workspace/.workflow-state.json to understand what exists.
        Read the project context and ALL skill files — especially
        react-native-quality, known-pitfalls, and integration-wiring.

        First survey what exists:
          find /workspace/src -name "*.ts" -o -name "*.tsx" | sort

        Read src/types/index.ts and src/stores/transportStore.ts before
        writing any component — you need to know the exact interface shapes.

        ## COMPONENTS (src/components/)

        ### 1. src/components/ErrorBoundary.tsx (~50 lines)
        Class component. MUST log errors in componentDidCatch — see pitfall P10.
        Shows friendly error message + "Try again" button that resets state.

        ### 2. src/components/Knob.tsx (~90 lines)
        MUST fix stale prop problem — see pitfall P8 and react-native-quality skill.
        useSharedValue for display rotation AND startValue for gesture base.
        Pan gesture: onStart captures baseValue, onUpdate computes from start.
        runOnJS(onChange) to call prop. accessibilityRole="adjustable".
        Display: rotary arc showing current value position (0=left, center=up, max=right).

        ### 3. src/components/Fader.tsx (~90 lines)
        Same stale-prop fix as Knob.
        Vertical pan gesture: translationY maps to value change.
        Visual: track bar + thumb indicator at correct position.
        Fill bar shows value (0% bottom, 100% top).
        accessibilityRole="adjustable".

        ### 4. src/components/TransportBar.tsx (~90 lines)
        Play/Stop button: animated scale spring on press.
        BPM display: tappable → calls tapTempo().
        BPM long press or separate +/- buttons for fine adjustment.
        Pattern indicator showing current pattern name (A1-A8).
        Swing display showing percentage.
        Uses useTransportStore selectors (one selector per value, not whole store).
        GestureDetector wrapping the play button for the scale animation.

        ### 5. src/components/StepGrid.tsx (~130 lines)
        MUST NOT use useSharedValue inside .map() — see pitfall P4.
        Use the pattern from the react-native-quality skill:
          - ONE useSharedValue<number> for currentStep
          - Extract StepCell as a separate React.memo() component
          - Pass stepSV as a prop to StepCell
        Track labels column on the left (width 80).
        Grid: ScrollView horizontal wrapping rows.
        Each cell: 44×44px, tap to toggle, opacity from velocity.
        Current step column: accent border color when playing.

        ### 6. src/components/DrumPads.tsx (~110 lines)
        Use PadButton component from the react-native-quality skill.
        8 pads in 2-column × 4-row grid.
        Tap: SamplerEngine.play() + Haptics.impactAsync(Medium) + scale animation.
        Each pad shows: track name, color accent border, last-hit velocity.
        onPress must go through runOnJS to call SamplerEngine.

        ### 7. src/components/SynthPanel.tsx (~120 lines)
        Waveform selector: 4 buttons (sine/saw/square/triangle).
          Active waveform button uses accent color background.
        ADSR section: 4 vertical Fader components, labeled A/D/S/R.
          Each fader is connected to synthStore.setParams().
        Filter section: Cutoff and Resonance Knob components.
          Both connected to synthStore.setParams().
        All controls read from useSynthStore('lead') params.

        ### 8. src/components/MixerChannel.tsx (~90 lines)
        Props: trackId, name.
        Pan Knob at top (min -1, max 1, center = 0).
        Volume Fader (tall, 160px height).
        Mute + Solo buttons with color state (muted = dimmed, soloed = accent).
        Peak meter: simple bar showing channel.volume as height.
        All connected to useMixerStore selectors.

        ### 9. src/components/MixerView.tsx (~60 lines)
        ScrollView horizontal.
        MixerChannel for each track (from useSequencerStore tracks).
        Master section at end: master volume fader + label.
        Master volume → mixerStore.setMasterVolume().

        ### 10. src/components/PatternSelector.tsx (~60 lines)
        8 buttons A1-A8.
        Active pattern highlighted with accent color.
        MUST use store action to change pattern — NO direct state mutation.
          onPress → useSequencerStore.getState().setCurrentPatternId(id)
          OR use the selector: const setCurrentPatternId = useSequencerStore(s => s.setCurrentPatternId)
        Long press: ActionSheet or Alert with Copy / Clear options.

        ## SCREENS (src/app/)

        ### 11. src/app/_layout.tsx (~35 lines)
        SafeAreaProvider root.
        useAudioSetup() called HERE and ONLY HERE.
        Loading state: centered text "Loading BeatForge..." with spinner.
        Error state: centered error message.
        Ready state: StatusBar (style="light") + ErrorBoundary wrapper + <Slot />.

        ### 12. src/app/(tabs)/_layout.tsx (~55 lines)
        5 Tabs.Screen: index, pads, synth, mixer, settings.
        Tab bar: backgroundColor '#1a1a1a', active '#ff6b35', inactive '#666'.
        Icons from @expo/vector-icons MaterialCommunityIcons:
          index → "view-grid-outline"
          pads → "drum"
          synth → "piano"
          mixer → "equalizer"
          settings → "cog-outline"
        headerShown: false.

        ### 13. src/app/(tabs)/index.tsx — Sequencer (~50 lines)
        SafeAreaView + ScrollView.
        Layout: TransportBar → PatternSelector → StepGrid.
        StepGrid fills remaining space.

        ### 14. src/app/(tabs)/pads.tsx — Pads (~50 lines)
        SafeAreaView.
        TransportBar at top.
        DrumPads centered in remaining space.
        Shows "Tap to play" hint text below pads.

        ### 15. src/app/(tabs)/synth.tsx — Synth (~60 lines)
        SafeAreaView.
        TransportBar at top.
        SynthPanel below.
        Row of note trigger buttons at bottom (C3, D3, E3, F3, G3, A3, B3, C4).
          Each button: onPress → SynthEngine.getInstance().play(note, 100).

        ### 16. src/app/(tabs)/mixer.tsx — Mixer (~40 lines)
        SafeAreaView.
        TransportBar at top.
        MixerView fills remaining space.

        ### 17. src/app/(tabs)/settings.tsx — Settings (~120 lines)
        REAL CONTROLS — not stubs. This screen must function completely.

        Section 1: Transport
          - BPM label + value display
          - Slider component (or TextInput) for BPM (60-240, step 1)
            → useTransportStore.setBpm()
          - Swing label + value display (0-100%)
          - Slider for swing (0-100, step 1)
            → useTransportStore.setSwing()

        Section 2: Project
          - TextInput for project name (local state)
          - "Save Project" TouchableOpacity → projectStore.saveProject()
          - "Load Project" TouchableOpacity → projectStore.loadProject()
          - "Reset All" TouchableOpacity → reset bpm=120, swing=0, load defaults

        Section 3: About
          - App name: "BeatForge"
          - Version: "v0.1.0"
          - "Made with Expo SDK 52"
          - Link or text: "Offline-first. No data collected."

        All sections use StyleSheet.create() with dark theme colors.
        Use ScrollView as root since content may overflow on small screens.

        ## Verification
        ```bash
        # No placeholder text
        grep -rn "will go here\|TODO\|stub\|placeholder\|coming soon" /workspace/src/
        # Must be EMPTY

        # Screen count
        find /workspace/src/app -name "*.tsx" | wc -l
        # Must be >= 7

        # Component count
        find /workspace/src/components -name "*.tsx" | wc -l
        # Must be >= 10

        # TypeScript
        cd /workspace && npx tsc --noEmit
        # Must be zero errors

        # ESLint hooks rules
        cd /workspace && npx eslint --ext .tsx src/components/StepGrid.tsx 2>&1
        # Must have zero errors (especially hooks violations)

        # No any
        grep -rn ": any\b\|as any" /workspace/src/
        # Must be EMPTY

        # Knob uses startValue pattern (not stale value)
        grep -n "startValue\|onStart" /workspace/src/components/Knob.tsx
        # Must show startValue being captured in onStart

        # PatternSelector uses store action, not direct mutation
        grep -n "setCurrentPatternId\|setState" /workspace/src/components/PatternSelector.tsx
        # Must show store action call, not direct property assignment
        ```

        ## Handoff state (update /workspace/.workflow-state.json):
          {
            "step": "implement",
            "completed": true,
            "screenCount": <number>,
            "componentCount": <number>,
            "tscClean": true,
            "eslintClean": true
          }
      execution:
        timeoutSeconds: 900
        maxAttempts: 1
        retryable: false
        continueOnError: false
        maxTurns: 10
        sessionGroup: dev-session

    # ── Step 3: Polish & Verify ───────────────────────────────────────────
    # Why changes from original:
    # - Added all 12 verification gates (not just tsc)
    # - Explicit test writing requirement with engine mocks
    # - Integration trace now checks real file contents (not just grep counts)
    # - README includes architecture decisions and known limitations
    # - continueOnError: false (original had true — failures should stop the build)
    - name: polish
      type: agent
      agentRef: daw-agent
      dependsOn:
        - implement
      prompt: |
        Read /workspace/.workflow-state.json to review implement results.
        Read the project context, ALL skill files, and the verification-gates
        skill. Run EVERY gate in that skill. Fix every failure found.

        ## Phase 1 — Run All Verification Gates
        Run all 12 gates from the verification-gates skill in order.
        For each failure, note the file and issue, then fix it.
        Do NOT skip any gate even if you believe it will pass.

        ## Phase 2 — Integration Trace (manual file reading)
        Read these files one by one. For each, verify the listed conditions:

        **_layout.tsx**: Contains useAudioSetup() call? isReady gate renders <Slot>?
        **useAudioSetup.ts**: onStep callback fires SamplerEngine.play()?
          setCurrentStep is called? Cleanup stops clock?
        **transportStore.ts**: play() calls AudioEngine.resume()?
          play() calls SequencerClock.start()? stop() calls SequencerClock.stop()?
          setBpm() restarts clock if playing?
        **SequencerClock.ts**: Uses nextStepTime and lookahead (not raw setInterval)?
          tick() method exists? Drift-correcting while loop exists?
        **AudioEngine.ts**: Uses SAMPLE_REQUIRES (static map)?
          Uses InterruptionModeIOS.DoNotMix (not deprecated constant)?
        **mixerStore.ts**: setVolume calls MixerEngine.setVolume()?
          setPan calls MixerEngine.setPan()?
        **projectStore.ts**: loadProject() syncs MixerEngine after loading?
        **PatternSelector.tsx**: Uses setCurrentPatternId store action?
          No direct state mutation?
        **Knob.tsx**: Uses startValue.value captured in onStart?
          No stale prop reference in onUpdate?
        **StepGrid.tsx**: No useSharedValue inside .map()?
          StepCell is a separate memo'd component?

        For each condition that FAILS, fix the file immediately.

        ## Phase 3 — Write Unit Tests
        Create these test files. Use the mock setup from src/test-utils/setup.ts.

        ### tests/engine/sequencerClock.test.ts
        Tests:
        - start() sets running=true
        - stop() sets running=false and resets stepIndex to 0
        - onStep callback receives sequential step indices 0-15 then wraps to 0
        - stop() then start() resets to step 0
        - swing=50 delays odd steps (test timing difference)

        ### tests/engine/mixerEngine.test.ts
        Tests:
        - getEffectiveVolume returns channel volume when no mute/solo
        - getEffectiveVolume returns 0 for muted channel
        - getEffectiveVolume returns channel volume for soloed channel
        - getEffectiveVolume returns 0 for non-soloed channel when another is soloed
        - setVolume clamps to [0,1]
        - setPan clamps to [-1,1]

        ### tests/utils/timing.test.ts
        Tests:
        - stepDurationMs(120) === 125
        - stepDurationMs(60) === 250
        - swingOffset(1, 50, 125) > 0  (odd step gets delay)
        - swingOffset(0, 50, 125) === 0  (even step not delayed)
        - swingOffset(1, 0, 125) === 0   (swing=0 means no delay)

        ### tests/stores/transportStore.test.ts
        Mock AudioEngine and SequencerClock. Tests:
        - play() calls AudioEngine.getInstance().resume()
        - play() calls SequencerClock.getInstance().start() with current bpm
        - stop() calls SequencerClock.getInstance().stop()
        - setBpm() restarts clock if isPlaying
        - tapTempo() with 2+ taps updates bpm

        Run tests after writing:
          cd /workspace && npx jest --passWithNoTests 2>&1 | tail -30

        ## Phase 4 — Documentation
        Create these files (all REAL content, not templates):

        ### README.md (~80 lines)
        - Project overview and feature list
        - Tech stack with specific versions
        - Setup: npm install && node scripts/generate-samples.js && npx expo start
        - Architecture overview: engines → stores → hooks → screens
        - Known limitations: expo-av synthesis (uses pre-rendered samples),
          setInterval timing (uses drift-correction but not Web Audio precision)
        - How to add new drum samples (update SAMPLE_REQUIRES and DEFAULT_TRACKS)
        - App Store build: npx eas build --platform all

        ### PRIVACY.md
        - No data collection, no analytics, no network requests
        - All data stored locally in AsyncStorage
        - No microphone access (mic permission not requested)
        - GDPR/CCPA: not applicable (no personal data processed)

        ### APPSTORE.md
        - App name: BeatForge — Beat Maker & Sequencer
        - Subtitle: Step Sequencer & Drum Machine
        - Keywords: beat maker, drum machine, sequencer, music, daw, rhythm, producer
        - Category: Music
        - Content rating: 4+
        - Description (200 words, marketing copy)
        - Build commands: npx eas build --platform ios --profile production
        - Required assets: icon (1024×1024), splash (2048×2048), screenshots

        ## Phase 5 — Final Verification (all 12 gates)
        Run every gate from the verification-gates skill one final time.
        Output the result of each gate. If any fails, fix and re-run.

        Final gate summary to write to stdout:
          "=== FINAL VERIFICATION SUMMARY ==="
          Gate 1 (tsc): PASS/FAIL
          Gate 2 (eslint): PASS/FAIL
          Gate 3 (file count): N files — PASS/FAIL
          Gate 4 (no stubs): PASS/FAIL
          Gate 5 (no any): PASS/FAIL
          Gate 6 (no shims): PASS/FAIL
          Gate 7 (zustand import): PASS/FAIL
          Gate 8 (no dynamic require): PASS/FAIL
          Gate 9 (engine wiring): PASS/FAIL
          Gate 10 (wav files): PASS/FAIL
          Gate 11 (tests pass): PASS/FAIL
          Gate 12 (integration trace): PASS/FAIL
          "=== BUILD READY: YES / NO ==="

        ## Handoff state (final update to /workspace/.workflow-state.json):
          {
            "step": "polish",
            "completed": true,
            "allGatesPassed": true,
            "testsPassed": true,
            "buildReady": true,
            "finalFileCount": <number>
          }
      execution:
        timeoutSeconds: 720
        maxAttempts: 1
        retryable: false
        continueOnError: false
        maxTurns: 8
        sessionGroup: dev-session
